<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 08 at 3:25PM CDT  by NWS Birmingham</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Jefferson County through 400 PM CDT...
At 325 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Center Point, or near Trussville, moving east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Northeastern Birmingham, Trussville, Gardendale, Center Point, Clay,
Pinson, Tarrant, Argo, Grayson Valley and Chalkville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
